If some operation (folding?) changes the screen rows and the decorations at the same time, the previous decorations can no longer be diffed against the decorations to-be-rendered to figure out what to classes to add/remove.

So rather than index by screenRow, this indexes by `lineNumberId`.

@nathansobo check it out

I work with long pathnames sometimes, and the pathname was hiding the syntax and other status indicator icons, so I made a fix in my `styles.less` that I thought would be a good addition for the main branch.

```
.status-bar .current-path {
  max-width: 100px;
  white-space: nowrap;
  overflow: hidden;
  display: block;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
}

.status-bar .current-path:hover {
  display: inline;
}

.status-bar .buffer-modified {
  display: none;
}
```

On hover, it shows the path, but otherwise doesn't go past 100px (+ the ellipsis). Changing the path to block though conflicts with the buffer modified asterisk, so I had to make it `display: none`. It was redundant anyway with the indicator in the tabs.
